# QR Code Generator

This is a simple QR Code Generator built using HTML, Tailwind CSS for styling, and a JavaScript library for generating QR codes.

## Features

- Enter any text or URL to generate a QR code.
- The generated QR code is displayed immediately after input.
- Responsive design using Tailwind CSS.

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- Tailwind CSS
- JavaScript
- [QRCode.js](https://davidshimjs.github.io/qrcodejs/)

## Getting Started

To run the QR Code Generator locally, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the repository:**

   
bash
   git clone https://github.com/yannickm260/QR_CodeGenerator.git
   cd qrcodegenerator
   

2. **Open the HTML file:**

   Open index.html in your web browser.

3. **Usage:**

   - Enter a text or a link in the input field.
   - The QR code will be generated and displayed below the input field.

## File Structure


qrcodegenerator/
├── index.html
└── qrcode.min.js  (Make sure to include this file in your project)

## Customization

Feel free to customize the styles and functionality as per your requirements. You can modify the Tailwind CSS classes in the HTML file to change the appearance of the application.

## Acknowledgments

- [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) for the utility-first CSS framework.
- [QRCode.js](https://davidshimjs.github.io/qrcodejs/) for the QR code generation library.
